Affected by the heavy rainfall in the upper reaches of the Yellow River, the water volume of the Hukou section at the intersection of Shaanxi Province and Shanxi Province has increased significantly, subsequently enhancing the magnificent waterfall landscape. The Hukou Waterfall is the largest yellow waterfall in the world. Watch the video to view the spectacular scenery. (If you want to contribute and have specific expertise, please contact us at nature@cgtn.com.)